com.google.api.gax.grpc

Interface ExecutorProvider


  • public interface ExecutorProvider
    Provides an interface to hold and create the Executor to be used. If the executor does not already exist, it will be constructed when getOrBuildExecutor() is called. Implementations of ExecutorProvider may choose to create a new ScheduledExecutorService for each call to getOrBuildExecutor(), or may return a fixed ScheduledExecutorService instance. In cases where the same ScheduledExecutorService instance is returned, for example by an ExecutorProvider created using the ServiceApiSettings provideExecutorWith(ScheduledExecutorService, boolean) method, and shouldAutoClose returns true, the getOrBuildExecutor() method will throw an IllegalStateException if it is called more than once. This is to prevent the same ScheduledExecutorService being closed prematurely when it is used by multiple client objects.

    • Method Detail

      • shouldAutoClose

        boolean shouldAutoClose()
        Indicates whether the channel should be closed by the containing API class.

      • getOrBuildExecutor

        ScheduledExecutorService getOrBuildExecutor()
        Get the executor to be used to connect to the service. The first time this is called, if the executor does not already exist, it will be created. If the ExecutorProvider is configured to return a fixed ScheduledExecutorService object and to return shouldAutoClose as true, then after the first call to getOrBuildExecutor(), subsequent calls should throw an IllegalStateException. See interface level docs for ExecutorProvider for more details.
